1 1 to whom school districts in the state provide a public education.
2 The aggregate current expenditures shall include without limitation
3 the following categories of expenditures:
4 1. Instruction provided by school district instructional staff;
5 2. Instruction provided through career and technology education
6 programs in comprehensive schools;
7 3. Instruction provided through concurrent classes that satisfy
8 graduation requirements;
9 4. Support services for students;
10 3. 5. Support services for instructional staff;
11 4. 6. Support services for general administration;
12 5. 7. Support services for school administration;
13 6. 8. Support services for business;
14 7. 9. Operation and maintenance of plant services;
15 8. 10. Student transportation services;
16 9. 11. Child nutrition services; and
17 10. 12. Enterprise services.
18 B. Aggregate current expenditures shall not include
19 expenditures for adult and community education, facilities
20 acquisition and construction services, debt services, property, and
21 other expenditures not related to the day-to-day operations.
22 C. The provisions of subsection A of this section shall apply
23 when related to the expenditure of public funds by educational and
24 governmental entities. When reporting or publishing the per-pupil
